snippet.textDisplay: We trust our life to other people all the time without realizing it. The Pilot, The Dr. the person driving the oncoming car. The person driving the car we are riding in. In the modern world the slightest mistake can cost lives and happen so fast that it is hard to believe. One of two things happened here. A pilot made a mistake or a mechanic made a mistake with tragic consequences. No matter what you do for a living, Whenever you drive,  please consider that countless strangers are counting on you to do a good job and do the right thing and make the right decisions.......Be careful all not just for yourself but for others.  Every stranger to you is precious to someone else. Be careful!
